cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.DS, cs.MA, cs.TR

This paper proposes a new on-line portfolio selection strategy that utilizes machine learning and AI techniques to exploit the mean reversion phenomenon in stock prices. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The paper also involves time series analysis, which suggests cs.MA (Multivariate Analysis) as another possible sub-category. Finally, the paper's focus on practical applicability and fast running time may suggest cs.TR (Trading and Market Microstructure) as a less likely but still possible sub-category.
